<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#666666><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uyukitaro.showPublicProfile>Yukitaro</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Global user</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>3/20/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>11:06:01 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Soulfire Charges important?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">My Soulfire had 0 charges of Complete Heal left in it..burned them on<br>
dragon runs.  Also, for those who want to know, we had a level 50<br>
enchanter cast allure on the Lich and were thus able to have our<br>
SK who had gotten the Phylactery turn it into the Lich.  Should they<br>
add a faction element, I think it is best to have an enchanter <br>
do the Book of Scale quest as they have all that fun faction stuff.<br>
However, to the best of my knowledge, there is no way to gain<br>
faction with the Lich of Miragul.  That is he scowled at all of us,<br>
and I read that someone who had raised the appropriate faction<br>
(with the Soul Trap? or Heretic?) still was scowled at.  Also, I<br>
completed the quest with warmly faction with DWK and Akera.<br>
I think it can be done with only amiably, as that's the level at<br>
which he will talk to you.  I was at kindly and upon turning in<br>
Soulfire and Ghoulbane and receiving both blessings I was warmly,<br>
so you get a big (and probably unimportant) faction increase with<br>
him for completing that part of the quest.  Good luck to the other<br>
Paladins out there who are close to obtaining their own Fiery<br>
Avengers.  It is a great challenge for all involved, but a worthwhile<br>
one, or it is a true test of oneself and one's friends.<br>
<br>
Yukitaro Antslayer, KEG GM, The Rathe</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#666666><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uandorion.showPublicProfile>Andorion</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ben2.ucla.edu/~berjd/Andorion.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Global user</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>3/20/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>11:48:04 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Soulfire Charges important?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Yukitaro, i know everyone's bitching about the FA... but how do YOU like it? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON STOP-->  I'm sure you've been using it left and right... how often does it proc?  Does the fact that it's 0.1 weight affect anything other than your stamina not decreasing?  What kinda hits do you get off with it?<br>
