-Andorion<br>
 berjd@ucla.edu</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#666666><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uyukitaro.showPublicProfile>Yukitaro</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Global user</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>3/21/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>4:24:40 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Soulfire Charges important?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I think my dex is at 115 or so right now and it procs regularly...<br>
sometimes a fight will pass without it going off, but then the next<br>
fight it'll proc 2-3 times, so the rate is fairly high.  My AC even<br>
with FA equipped is in the upper 800s self buffed, so until I pull<br>
again in fear or hate next, I'll hold off on going back to sprinkler/<br>
shield of rainbow hues.  The average hit is of course 74, with<br>
a fair amount of 11s (yes, elevens.. isn't that depressing) sprinkled<br>
in there with a good amount of hits for over 100... damn those<br>
are nice to see.  My max hit was for 133.  All in all I'm very happy<br>
with the sword.  However, I've said it before and I'll say it again..<br>
I wish it was 1hs so I could use my godly shield(s) with it.  I<br>
don't see how making it 1hs would affect game balance in any <br>
noticeable way since there won't ever be a large number of<br>
Paladins with the sword given the difficulty of the quest.<br>
<br>
